## Git Workflow

> Full details: [docs/git-workflow.md](docs/git-workflow.md)

### Branch Naming

```
feature/<issue-number>-<short-description>
fix/<issue-number>-<short-description>
refactor/<issue-number>-<short-description>
```

### Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

Refs: #<issue-number>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`

### PR Requirements

- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Evaluation score >= 7.5 (PASS), no category below 7
- [ ] No security checklist violations
- [ ] PR description includes issue reference

---

## Security Checklist

> Full details: [docs/security-checklist.md.template](docs/security-checklist.md.template)

Every PR must verify:

1. **Authentication & Authorization** — Endpoint access control verified
2. **Input Validation** — SQL/NoSQL/external input properly escaped
3. **Data Exposure** — No sensitive data in logs or responses
4. **Infrastructure Isolation** — Internal service ports not exposed
5. **Dependency Vulnerabilities** — External library CVEs checked

